entry.def: Parliamentary is used to describe things that are connected with a parliament or with Members of Parliament.

example.ex: He used his influence to make sure she was not selected as a parliamentary candidate.

means.word_mean: 1. relating to or having the nature of a parliament;
2. having the supreme legislative power resting with a body of cabinet ministers chosen from and responsible to the legislature or parliament;
3. in accord with rules and customs of a legislative or deliberative assembly;
